From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 19:31:08 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: add hot/cold field markers to compact layout

Third increment of the C++MG 'compact' feature: optional per-field
'hot' / 'cold' placement markers refine the compact ordering.

Surface: inside a record, a field may be prefixed with 'hot' or 'cold',
e.g. 'hot double position;' or 'cold char name[8];'. 'hot' fields are
placed first (toward the first cache line(s)); 'cold' fields last.
Padding is still minimized within each of the hot / unmarked / cold
groups, but across groups hotness takes priority over padding -- marking
fields hot can make a struct larger, which is the intended tradeoff.

Implementation avoids touching any widely-included AST header (FieldDecl
has no spare state and Decl.h has the largest blast radius). Instead:
- Parser::ParseCXXClassMemberDeclaration is now a thin wrapper that
  consumes a leading hot/cold keyword and records the hint in a new
  Parser-member map (DenseMap<const FieldDecl*, CXXMGHotness>); the real
  body moved to ParseCXXClassMemberDeclarationImpl.
- cxxmg::applyCompactLayout gained a hotness lookup (llvm::function_ref);
  computeCompactOrdering now partitions fields into hot / middle / cold,
  stable-sorting each by descending alignment, then concatenates them.
- CXXMGHotness lives in CXXMGLayout.h (folded into the existing files, so
  no CMakeLists change and a small incremental rebuild).

Tests (clang/test/CXXMG/compact/, one scenario per file):
- compact-hot-first-cold-last.cpp: layout dump shows hot first, cold last.
- compact-cold-pushed-to-tail.cpp: cold field goes last, rest padding-min.
- compact-hot-group-padding-min.cpp: hot group is padding-min internally.
- compact-hot-priority-over-padding.cpp: hot-first can exceed the pure
  padding-minimized size.

diff --git a/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h b/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h
index 3e3fcf854..4adfeac66 100644
--- a/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h
+++ b/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h
@@ -16,12 +16,22 @@
 #ifndef LLVM_CLANG_AST_CXXMGLAYOUT_H
 #define LLVM_CLANG_AST_CXXMGLAYOUT_H
 
+#include "llvm/ADT/STLFunctionalExtras.h"
+
 namespace clang {
 class ASTContext;
+class FieldDecl;
 class RecordDecl;
 
 namespace cxxmg {
 
+/// Field-placement hint requested by the C++MG `hot` / `cold` field markers.
+enum class CXXMGHotness : unsigned char {
+  None = 0, ///< Unmarked field: ordered purely to minimize padding.
+  Hot = 1,  ///< `hot`: pack toward the first cache line(s).
+  Cold = 2, ///< `cold`: push toward the tail.
+};
+
 /// Apply the C++MG `compact` layout to \p RD: reorder its fields to minimize
 /// padding (a stable sort by descending alignment) and commit the new order
 /// through RecordDecl::reorderDecls.
@@ -35,8 +45,15 @@ namespace cxxmg {
 /// dependent records, records with bases or a vptr, bitfields, anonymous
 /// members, or fewer than two reorderable fields.
 ///
+/// Optional `hot`/`cold` field markers refine the order: `hot` fields are
+/// placed first (toward the first cache line(s)) and `cold` fields last, with
+/// padding minimized within each group. \p GetHotness returns the hint for a
+/// given field (CXXMGHotness::None for unmarked fields).
+///
 /// \returns true if the record's field order was changed.
-bool applyCompactLayout(const ASTContext &Context, RecordDecl *RD);
+bool applyCompactLayout(
+    const ASTContext &Context, RecordDecl *RD,
+    llvm::function_ref<CXXMGHotness(const FieldDecl *)> GetHotness);
 
 } // namespace cxxmg
 } // namespace clang
